//go:build voice_e2e

// Package session contains end-to-end integration tests for the full voice
// pipeline: Energy VAD → Whisper STT (native CGO) → Address Detection →
// NPC Agent → Cascade Engine (mock LLM + mock TTS) → Priority Mixer →
// Loopback Output.
//
// Test audio is generated by ElevenLabs TTS. The LLM and TTS stages use
// mocks to keep the test deterministic. Energy-based VAD is used instead of
// Silero due to an ONNX Runtime 1.24 compatibility issue (documented in
// TestVoiceE2E_SileroVAD).
//
// NOTE: Whisper.cpp Go bindings have an inherent data race in
// registerProgressCallback (upstream issue). These tests must NOT run with
// -race when using parallel Whisper sessions. The full-pipeline tests
// (NPC addressing, speaker switching, etc.) run sequentially within each
// test function.
//
// Prerequisites:
//   - whisper.cpp: make whisper-libs && export C_INCLUDE_PATH=/tmp/whisper-install/include LIBRARY_PATH=/tmp/whisper-install/lib
//   - Whisper model: ggml-base.en.bin at /tmp/whisper-models/ggml-base.en.bin
//   - Test audio: testdata/audio/*.pcm (generated by ElevenLabs TTS)
//
// Run: go test -tags voice_e2e -count=1 -run TestVoiceE2E -v -timeout 300s ./internal/session/
package session

